## Optimising with respect to demographic-distance weighting

Can a hybrid estimate --- drawing on data from areas outside the CED --- outperform the simple/unweighted scheme that samples from `AREAENUM` pps (probability proportional to size).

We let data points from other `AREAENUM` contribute to the synthetic data we sample for a given CED, by using sample weights for other `AREAENUM` that are a decreasing function of the demographic distance measure among `AREAENUM`.

```{r}
#| eval: false
obj_func <- function(theta,obj){
  weighted_sample_ced(obj$Division[1],theta) %>% 
    get_marginals() %>% 
    compare_marginals() %>% 
    total_kl()
}

do_optim <- function(obj){
  tmp <- ced_sa4 %>% semi_join(obj,by = "Division")
  
  ## try some Metropolis/SA to get started
  z0 <- optim(par = c(0,1),
              fn = obj_func,
              obj = tmp,
              method = "SANN",
              control = list(maxit = 250))
  
  ## then switch to Nelder-Mead
  z <- optim(par = z0$par,
             fn = obj_func,
             obj = tmp,
             control = list()
             )
  return(z)
}

## loop over each division and store optimal weighting parameters and total KL
z <- keySeats %>% 
  group_nest(Division,keep = TRUE) %>% 
  mutate(z = future_map(
    .x = data,
    .f = ~do_optim(.x))
    ) %>% 
  ungroup()
```

What kind of weighting functions are implied by the parameter estimates?
```{r}
#| eval: false
theta <- z %>% unnest_wider(z) %>% select(Division,par) %>% unnest_wider(par,names_sep = "_")

getWeights_do <- function(obj,theta1,theta2){
  theta <- c(theta1,theta2)

    w <- areaenum_dist %>%
      filter(AREAENUM == obj$AREAENUM) %>%
      mutate(prob_of_selection = 1/exp(theta[1] + theta[2]*distance))
  
    curf_weight <- curf %>%
      filter(!(AGEP %in% as.character(0:17))) %>%
      filter(CITP == "Australian") %>%
      count(AREAENUM) %>%
      left_join(w %>%
                  select(j, w = prob_of_selection, distance),
                by = c("AREAENUM" = "j")
                ) %>% 
      mutate(p = w*n/sum(n)) %>% 
      mutate(p2 = p/sum(p))
    
  return(curf_weight) 
}

getWeights <- function(obj){
    ced_sa4 %>% 
    filter(Division == obj$Division) %>% 
    group_nest(AREAENUM,keep = TRUE) %>% 
    mutate(d = map(.x = data,
                   .f = ~getWeights_do(.x,obj$par_1,obj$par_2))) %>% 
    ungroup() %>% 
    unnest(c(d),
           names_sep = "_")
}

theta <- theta %>% 
  group_nest(Division,keep = TRUE) %>% 
  mutate(d = future_map(.x = data,
                        .f = ~getWeights(.x))) %>% 
  ungroup()
```

## Optimisation via neural net weighting of covariates

We use a "black-box" optimisation strategy to find weights as a function of CURF variables, so as to minimize KL divergences on CED marginals.

```{r}
#| eval: false
library(rsample)
library(tensorflow)
library(tfdatasets)
library(keras)

get_areaenum_features <- function(obj){
  f <- sample_curf_simple(obj) %>% 
    select(SEXP, AGEP, OCCP, RELP_collapsed, UNI, INCP_original) %>% 
    mutate(AGEP = droplevels(AGEP)) %>% 
    mutate(
      
      across(
        where( ~ !is.factor(.x)),
        factor
      ),
      
      across(
        where(is.factor),
        droplevels
        )
      
    )
  
  return(f)
}

get_division_data <- function(obj){
  f <- ced_sa4 %>% 
    filter(Division == obj$Division) %>% 
    group_nest(AREAENUM,keep = TRUE) %>% 
    mutate(
      f = map(.x = data,
                   .f = ~get_areaenum_features(.x)
              )
      ) %>% 
    ungroup() %>% 
    unnest(f) %>% 
    select(-data) 
  
  return(f)
}

nn_fit <- function(obj){
  f <- get_division_data(obj)
  levelSet <- lapply(f,levels) %>%
    lapply(.,as_tibble) %>%
    bind_rows(.,.id = "var") %>% 
    rename(j = value)
  
  dataset <- recipe(f %>% select(-AREAENUM)) %>% 
    step_dummy(recipes::all_nominal(),one_hot = TRUE) %>%
    prep() %>% 
    bake(new_data = NULL)

  split <- initial_split(dataset,0.9)
  train_dataset <- training(split)
  test_dataset <- testing(split)
  
  actuals <- left_join(
    levelSet,
    ced_marginals %>%
      filter(Division == obj$Division) %>%
      filter(
        var %in% c("SEXP",
                   "AGEP",
                   "OCCP",
                   "RELP_collapsed",
                   "uni",
                   "INCP")
      ) %>%
      mutate(
        var = if_else(var == "uni", "UNI", var),
        var = if_else(var == "INCP", "INCP_original", var)
      ),
    by = c("var","j")
  )
  p_true <- as_tensor(actuals$p,dtype = "float32")
    
  x <- as.matrix(train_dataset)
  n <- dim(x)[1]
  k <- dim(x)[2]
  x_tensor <- as_tensor(x,dtype = "float32")
  x_keras_tensor <- tf$keras$Input(shape = k)
  
  y <- as_tensor(as.matrix(actuals$p),dtype = "float32")
  z <- as_tensor(matrix(1,n,1),dtype = "float32")
  
  get_marginals <- function(w){
    tf$reduce_mean(tf$reduce_sum(x_tensor * w, axis = 0L), axis = 0L)
  }
  
  d0 <- layer_input(shape = shape(k),
                    name = "data")
  outputs <- d0 %>%
    layer_dense(units = 2*k, name = "dense_1") %>%
    layer_dense(units = 32,  activation = "relu",    name = "dense_3") %>%
    layer_dense(units = 1,  activation = "sigmoid", name = "dense_4")
  
  my_loss <- function(y_dummy,pred){
    l_fn <- tf_function(function(y_dummy,pred){
      p_pred <- k_sum(x_tensor * pred,axis = 1) * 1/k_sum(pred)
      kl <- p_true * log(p_true/p_pred)
      k_sum(kl)
      })
    
    return(l_fn)
  }
  
  my_loss2 <- function(y_dummy,pred){
    w <- k_exp(pred)/k_sum(k_exp(pred)) * n
    #w <- pred
    #tf$print(k_mean(w))
    #tf$print(k_min(w))
    #tf$print(k_max(w))
    p_pred <- k_sum(x_tensor * w,axis = 1)/n
    k_sum(p_true * k_log(p_true/p_pred))
  }
  
  model <- keras_model_sequential() %>% 
    layer_dense(units = 2273, activation = "linear", name = "dense_1",input_shape = k) %>%
    layer_dense(units = 1,  name = "dense_4",input_shape = 2273)
    
  model %>% 
    compile(
      optimizer = "adam",
      loss = my_loss2
    )

  model %>% 
    fit(x=x_tensor,
        y=z,
        epochs = 50E3,
        verbose=1,
        batch_size = n)
  
  return(model) 
}

nn_fit(keySeats %>% slice(1))
```
